  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until it's softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> stock mix</strong> in 550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[825ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>onion has softened, add your <strong>arborio rice </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Add a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in oil</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> chives </strong>finely</p><p>Cut your<strong> smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the risotto has had 20 min, add the<strong> drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>smoked basa pieces</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-10 min further or until the basa is cooked through, all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is tender</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, stir through<strong> half </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and most of the <strong>chives </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) then discard the bay leaf[ves]<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>smoked basa & sweetcorn risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-risotto-with-sweetcorn-and-chives/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>smoked basa & sweetcorn risotto, </strong>then garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chives </strong>and <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
